<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>2<percent/> of 1162</li> 
<li>32<percent/> of 207</li> 
<li>84<percent/> of 21</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>B: 32<percent/> of 207</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{84}\%\cdot{21}={17.64}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{32}\%\cdot{207}={66.24}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{2}\%\cdot{1162}={23.24}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 32<percent/> of 207 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
